## Open Questions for Your Review

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1 — Distribution Algorithm**: The proposed skip-interval approach is one strategy. An alternative is a **weekly-budget approach** (allocate N skips per week proportionally). Which style do you prefer, or should I present both in detail?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2 — Slot Types**: Should slot types be **global** (shared across all semesters, like event types) or **per-semester** (each semester defines its own types)?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3 — Import Scope**: For V1.1, should we support **both PDF and image** import for timetables, or start with PDF-only and add image/OCR in a later version? PDF parsing is significantly more reliable than OCR.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q4 — Milestone Ordering**: Goals 1 (Import) and Goal 2+3 (Engine changes) are independent. Would you prefer engine improvements first (M1→M2) then import (M3→M5), or interleave them differently?

> [!WARNING]
> **Q5 — Tesseract Dependency**: Tesseract OCR requires installing a system binary (`tesseract-ocr`). This adds a setup step for new developers. Are you comfortable with this dependency, or should we explore a pure-Python alternative (lower accuracy but zero system deps)?
